walkGenerators.base

Class MemoryParser

  • java.lang.Object
    • walkGenerators.base.MemoryParser
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IParser
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    NtMemoryParser, NxMemoryParser

    public abstract class MemoryParser
extends Object
implements IParser
    Memory based parser using the TripleDataSetMemory data structure. These kind of parsers load the complete model into memory.

      • generateWeightedMidWalksForEntity

        public List<String> generateWeightedMidWalksForEntity(String entity,
                                                      int depth,
                                                      int numberOfWalks)
        Weighted mid walk: If there are more options to go forward, it is more likely to go forward.
        Parameters:
        entity - The entity for which walks shall be generated.
        depth - The depth of the walk. Depth is defined as hop to the next node. A walk of depth 1 will have three walk components.
        numberOfWalks - Number of walks to be performed per entity.
        Returns:
        List of walks.

      • generateWeightedMidWalkForEntityAsArray

        Walks of length 1, i.e., walks that contain only one node, are ignored.
        Parameters:
        entity - The entity for which walks shall be generated.
        depth - The depth of each walk (where the depth is the number of hops).
        numberOfWalks - The number of walks to be performed.
        Returns:
        A data structure describing the walks.

      • convertToStringWalksDuplicateFree

        public List<String> convertToStringWalksDuplicateFree(List<List<String>> dataStructureToConvert)
        Given a list of walks where a walk is represented as a List of strings, this method will convert that into a list of strings where a walk is one string (and the elements are separated by spaces). The lists are duplicate free.
        Parameters:
        dataStructureToConvert - The data structure that shall be converted.
        Returns:
        Data structure converted to string list.
